{"bookResponse":{"bookId":"0c251ad50457d703e205d5870b422824","locale":"en_US","title":"macOS User Guide","meta":{"productVersion":"10.14","platformOSVersion":"10.14","icon":"https://help.apple.com/assets/5BFDD3F8094622802EEE504F/5BFDD3F9094622802EEE5056/en_US/937fa92677a2c49a18fa81070e5d8419.png","build_date":"Thu Mar 07 23:06:15 GMT 2019","product":"mac-help","creationDate":"Fri Aug 24 07:00:00 GMT 2018","lastModifiedDate":"Mon Mar 25 22:02:11 GMT 2019","contentType":"book","framework":"duck-12.5.0:goose-2.12.5:cuckoo-3.0.10"},"tocId":"MH43558","bookInfo":{"versionsDetails":[{"productVersion":"10.14","displayVersion":"macOS Mojave 10.14","platform":"mac","platformOSVersion":"10.14"},{"productVersion":"10.13","displayVersion":"macOS High Sierra","platform":"mac","platformOSVersion":"10.13"}]},"articles":[{"articleId":{"id":"BK_0C251AD50457D703E205D5870B422824_MCHL732D3C0A","locale":"en_US"},"meta":{"createDate":"Fri Aug 24 07:00:00 GMT 2018","lastModifiedDate":"Mon Mar 25 22:02:11 GMT 2019","publishedDate":"Mon Mar 25 22:02:11 GMT 2019","contentType":"book","archive":"false","ownerName":"apd migration","modifiedBy":"apd migration","version":"1","unPublished":false},"content":{"main":{"title":"Pick up where you left off with Handoff on Mac","summary":"On your Mac, automatically pass what you’re working on to your nearby devices. All devices must be set up to use Handoff."},"sections":[{"level":"1","text":"<body dir=\"ltr\" id=\"mchl732d3c0a\" class=\"AppleTopic apd-topic\" data-istaskopen=\"true\" data-designversion=\"2\" lang=\"en\"><a name=\"mchl732d3c0a\"></a><figure class=\"topicIcon\"><img src=\"https://help.apple.com/assets/5BFDD3F8094622802EEE504F/5BFDD3F9094622802EEE5056/en_US/937fa92677a2c49a18fa81070e5d8419.png\" alt=\"\" height=\"30\" width=\"30\" originalImageName=\"SharedGlobalArt/AppIconDefault_MacHelp.png\"></figure><h1>Pick up where you left off with Handoff on Mac</h1><p>With Handoff, you can start something on one device (Mac, iOS, or Apple Watch) and then pick it up on another without losing focus on what you’re doing. For example, look at a webpage on your iPhone, then pick up where you left off in Safari on your Mac. You can use Handoff with many Apple apps—for example, Calendar, Contacts, Pages, or Safari. Some third-party apps may also work with Handoff.</p><figure><img src=\"https://help.apple.com/assets/5BFDD3F8094622802EEE504F/5BFDD3F9094622802EEE5056/en_US/b5836874e5ec71781b9d5fc6f458dd44.png\" alt=\"An app’s Handoff icon from iPhone at the left side of the Dock.\" height=\"137\" width=\"297\" originalImageName=\"Art/S0014_Handoff.png\"></figure><p>To use Handoff, your devices must meet <a href=\"https://support.apple.com/guide/?platform=mac&amp;product=mac-help&amp;vanityname=continuity&amp;version=10.14&amp;locale=en_US&amp;topicid=GLOSE229DF1E&amp;type=ddm&amp;platformOSVersion=10.14&amp;aside=true\" class=\"xRef Aside\">Continuity</a> system requirements. They must also have Wi-Fi, Bluetooth, and Handoff turned on in System Preferences (on your Mac) and in Settings (on your iOS devices). You must be <a href=\"https://support.apple.com/guide/?platform=mac&amp;product=mac-help&amp;vanityname=set-up-icloud&amp;version=10.14&amp;locale=en_US&amp;topicid=MH36834&amp;type=ddm&amp;platformOSVersion=10.14\" class=\"xRef AppleTopic\">signed in to iCloud</a> using the same <a href=\"https://support.apple.com/guide/?platform=mac&amp;product=mac-help&amp;vanityname=apple-id&amp;version=10.14&amp;locale=en_US&amp;topicid=MH22612FA790&amp;type=ddm&amp;platformOSVersion=10.14&amp;aside=true\" class=\"xRef Aside\">Apple ID</a> on all your devices. </p><div class=\"Alert\"><p class=\"Tip\"><strong class=\"tip\">Tip: </strong>When Handoff is on, you can <a href=\"https://support.apple.com/guide/?platform=mac&amp;product=mac-help&amp;vanityname=copy-and-paste-between-devices&amp;version=10.14&amp;locale=en_US&amp;topicid=MCHL70368996&amp;type=ddm&amp;platformOSVersion=10.14\" class=\"xRef AppleTopic\">use Universal Clipboard</a> to copy and paste text, images, photos, and videos across devices. You can also copy files between Mac computers.</p></div><div id=\"apd98397effbea64\" class=\"Task\"><h2 role=\"button\" aria-controls=\"aria-apd98397effbea64\" aria-expanded=\"true\" class=\"Name\">Turn Handoff on or off</h2><div class=\"TaskBody\" role=\"region\" aria-hidden=\"false\" id=\"aria-apd98397effbea64\"><div class=\"Alert\"><p class=\"Note\"><em>Note: </em>If you don’t see a Handoff option on your device, it doesn’t work with Handoff.</p></div><ul class=\"ListSingle\"><li><p><em>On your Mac: </em>Choose Apple menu <img src=\"https://help.apple.com/assets/5BFDD3F8094622802EEE504F/5BFDD3F9094622802EEE5056/en_US/e043ddf1a45711e13f0b30612db65e21.png\" alt=\"\" height=\"30\" width=\"26\" originalImageName=\"SharedGlobalArt/IL_AppleLogo.png\"> &gt; System Preferences, click General, then select “Allow Handoff between this Mac and your iCloud devices” (below “Recent items”). To turn it off, deselect the option.</p><p><a href=\"x-help-action://openPrefPane?bundleId=com.apple.preference.general\" class=\"URL\">Open General preferences for me</a></p></li><li><p><em>On iPad, iPhone, or iPod touch: </em>Go to Settings &gt; General &gt; Handoff, then tap to turn on Handoff. To turn it off, tap the option.</p></li><li><p><em>On Apple Watch: </em>Open the Watch app on iPhone, go to My Watch &gt; General, then tap to turn on Enable Handoff. To turn it off, tap the option.</p></li></ul></div></div><div id=\"apd453437190cfe4\" class=\"Task\"><h2 role=\"button\" aria-controls=\"aria-apd453437190cfe4\" aria-expanded=\"true\" class=\"Name\">Hand off between devices</h2><div class=\"TaskBody\" role=\"region\" aria-hidden=\"false\" id=\"aria-apd453437190cfe4\"><ul class=\"ListSingle\"><li><p><em>From your Mac to an iOS device: </em>The Handoff icon of the app you’re using on your Mac appears on your iPhone (at the bottom of the app switcher) or your iPad or iPod touch (at the end of the Dock). Tap to continue working in the app.</p></li><li><p><em>From an iOS device or Apple Watch to your Mac: </em>The Handoff icon of the app you’re using on your iPad, iPhone, iPod touch, or Apple Watch appears on your Mac at the left end of the Dock (or the top, depending on the Dock position). Click the icon to continue working in the app.</p><p>You can also press Command-Tab to <a href=\"https://support.apple.com/guide/?platform=mac&amp;product=mac-help&amp;vanityname=manage-windows&amp;version=10.14&amp;locale=en_US&amp;topicid=MCHLP2469&amp;type=ddm&amp;platformOSVersion=10.14\" class=\"xRef AppleTopic\">quickly switch to the app</a> that has the Handoff icon.</p></li></ul></div></div><div class=\"LinkUniversal\"><strong>See also</strong><a href=\"https://support.apple.com/guide/?platform=mac&amp;product=mac-help&amp;vanityname=continuity&amp;version=10.14&amp;locale=en_US&amp;topicid=MCHL1D734309&amp;type=ddm&amp;platformOSVersion=10.14\" class=\"xRef AppleTopic\">Use Continuity to work across Apple devices</a><a href=\"https://support.apple.com/HT204681\" class=\"URL\">Apple Support article: Use Continuity to connect your Mac, iPhone, iPad, iPod touch, and Apple Watch</a><a href=\"https://support.apple.com/guide/?platform=mac&amp;product=mac-help&amp;vanityname=turn-bluetooth-on-or-off&amp;version=10.14&amp;locale=en_US&amp;topicid=BLTH1008&amp;type=ddm&amp;platformOSVersion=10.14\" class=\"xRef AppleTopic\">Turn Bluetooth on or off on Mac</a><a href=\"https://support.apple.com/guide/?platform=mac&amp;product=mac-help&amp;vanityname=dock&amp;version=10.14&amp;locale=en_US&amp;topicid=MH35859&amp;type=ddm&amp;platformOSVersion=10.14\" class=\"xRef AppleTopic\">Use the Dock on Mac</a><a href=\"https://support.apple.com/guide/?platform=mac&amp;product=mac-help&amp;vanityname=send-files-between-devices-with-airdrop&amp;version=10.14&amp;locale=en_US&amp;topicid=MH35868&amp;type=ddm&amp;platformOSVersion=10.14\" class=\"xRef AppleTopic\">Use AirDrop on your Mac to send files to devices near you</a><a href=\"https://support.apple.com/guide/?platform=mac&amp;product=mac-help&amp;vanityname=what-is-icloud&amp;version=10.14&amp;locale=en_US&amp;topicid=MH36832&amp;type=ddm&amp;platformOSVersion=10.14\" class=\"xRef AppleTopic\">What is iCloud?</a></div></body>","tags":[{"type":"audience","refKey":"PUBLIC_USERS","tagPath":"audience/PUBLIC_USERS","title":"Public"}]}]},"categoryInfo":{"categories":["DisplayVersion/macOS Mojave 10.14","IP-Meta/DesignVersion/DesignVersion2","platform/mac","ContentMode/liveContent","ArchivalStatus/Unarchived","MetaFollow/MetaFollowOFF","ExternalIndex/ExternalIndexON","SupportSearchIndex/SupportSearchIndexON"],"categoryDictionaries":[{"key":"SupportSearchIndexON","name":"SupportSearchIndexON","englishName":"SupportSearchIndexON","displayName":"SupportSearchIndexON","articleCount":"3950"},{"key":"liveContent","name":"Live Content","englishName":"Live Content","displayName":"Live Content","articleCount":"7864"},{"key":"IP-Meta","name":"IP-Meta","englishName":"IP-Meta","displayName":"IP-Meta","articleCount":"0"},{"key":"Unarchived","name":"Unarchived","englishName":"Unarchived","displayName":"Unarchived","articleCount":"10186"},{"key":"ContentMode","name":"ContentMode","englishName":"ContentMode","displayName":"ContentMode","articleCount":"0"},{"key":"ExternalIndexON","name":"ExternalIndexON","englishName":"ExternalIndexON","displayName":"ExternalIndexON","articleCount":"4683"},{"key":"DesignVersion2","name":"DesignVersion 2","englishName":"DesignVersion 2","displayName":"DesignVersion 2","articleCount":"7818"},{"key":"MetaFollow","name":"MetaFollow","englishName":"MetaFollow","displayName":"MetaFollow","articleCount":"0"},{"key":"ExternalIndex","name":"ExternalIndex","englishName":"ExternalIndex","displayName":"ExternalIndex","articleCount":"0"},{"key":"DesignVersion","name":"DesignVersion","englishName":"DesignVersion","displayName":"DesignVersion","articleCount":"0"},{"key":"mac","name":"mac","englishName":"mac"